Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.96,0:00:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out of here quickly!\NThe police are coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.03,0:00:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.80,0:00:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Dresden... Wait at the public square\Nin front of the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.91,0:00:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me the message. Quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.24,0:00:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Here...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.98,0:00:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,edok Bridge... Three frogs?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.22,0:00:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And my father also said,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.09,0:00:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,"If the monster you're\Nchasing is a twin..."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.99,0:00:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The mother of the twins\Nis still alive in Prague.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.25,0:02:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.29,0:02:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.33,0:02:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.40,0:02:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, here you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.93,0:02:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice!\NThere it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.10,0:02:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop.\NGive it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.70,0:02:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Pass it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.57,0:02:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it going Mr. Grimmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.54,0:02:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you find the data\Nyou were looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.25,0:02:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The school's structure\Nhas completely changed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.82,0:02:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,since the reunification of\NEast and West Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.88,0:02:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have any earlier data.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.85,0:02:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you for your time,\NPrincipal Garbrecht.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.92,0:02:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unusual to have retained\Nthis much data.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.56,0:03:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When the Berlin Wall fell,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.13,0:03:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,most of East Germany's\Nunsavory data disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.14,0:03:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.71,0:03:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I am certain that children were abused\Nin East Germany's orphanages.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.11,0:03:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't find any\Ninformation to prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.98,0:03:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I can imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.82,0:03:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,East German orphanages\Nwere usually managed by
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.49,0:03:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the Ministry of Public Health\Nand Welfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.99,0:03:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But there were problems when\Nthe children's parents were
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.36,0:03:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminals, anti-government protesters,\Nspies, defectors to the west,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.30,0:03:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or those who were caught\Ntrying to cross the border.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.70,0:03:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The orphanages where\Nthese children were kept
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.47,0:03:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,were managed by the infamous\NInternal Affairs Ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.58,0:03:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No one knows how much abuse and\Ninhumane personality corrections
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.38,0:03:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,those children endured there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.68,0:03:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been trying to gather\Nas much information as I can
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.05,0:04:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I can find out exactly\Nwhat happened there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.39,0:04:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly what, huh? I see.\NThat's a tedious investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.46,0:04:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of those involved have\Neither passed away or kept silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.20,0:04:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Even Mr. Schnurr,\Nthe instructor here...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.27,0:04:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Schnurr?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.34,0:04:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a teacher at\NEast Germany's 62 Kinderheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.82,0:04:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked him for an interview,\Nbut he refused.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.29,0:04:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.02,0:04:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There is the possibility that Mr. Schnurr\Nabused children while in East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.60,0:04:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Is it all right if\NI make copies of this data?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.54,0:04:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, go right ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.37,0:04:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer, you're really a journalist\Nfrom West Germany, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.21,0:04:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I'm from this side.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.35,0:04:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a reporter for\Na newspaper in Leipzig.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.82,0:05:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... I never expected a civil libertarian\Nlike you to be from the East.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.59,0:05:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.16,0:05:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,During that time, I flew around the world\Nas a special overseas correspondent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.77,0:05:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They were missions given\Nto me by the government.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.50,0:05:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand\Nwhat I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.37,0:05:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.44,0:05:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Heave!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.78,0:05:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a big bag you're carrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.68,0:05:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's packed with data I've collected\Nfrom around East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.18,0:05:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to\Nreading a good article.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.45,0:05:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So where are you going now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.82,0:05:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,To Prague, in the Czech Republic.\NThank you for your help, Director.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.54,0:06:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You were treated\Npretty badly back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.42,0:06:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they end up\Ntaking your shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.79,0:06:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.17,0:06:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,People can live without shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.07,0:06:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We were born barefoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.04,0:06:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.58,0:06:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who pick on people\Nby taking their shoes...are terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.72,0:06:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to cry over what\Nthose terrible guys have done to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.62,0:06:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Were they so big that\Nthey were an inconvenience?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.56,0:07:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm... Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.06,0:07:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.43,0:07:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.80,0:07:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.47,0:07:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... I have a problem.\NMy bag with my passport was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.97,0:07:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Your passport? That's bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.78,0:07:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It is. I was going to see\Nmy younger sister in Vienna.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.08,0:07:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, I received word\Nthat she had collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.42,0:07:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Collapsed?\NYou should go quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.32,0:07:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You should go to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.49,0:07:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I-I already did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.03,0:08:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, right now...my sister doesn't\Nhave any money for a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.87,0:08:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... That's terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.50,0:08:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,My bag also had my wallet in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.37,0:08:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.67,0:08:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go, but my sister will\Nbe all right if I send money.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.58,0:08:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't even do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.02,0:08:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How much do you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.08,0:08:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...you don't need to!\NI don't need too much money!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.76,0:08:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I just need money to\Npay for a doctor to see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.86,0:08:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I can only give this much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.23,0:08:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-Thank you. Danke schön!\NI'll pay you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.17,0:08:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Write your address here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.24,0:08:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's all right.\NIf it will help your sister get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.08,0:08:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you! God bless you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.58,0:08:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care of your sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.82,0:08:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you\Ngive money to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.42,0:08:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.12,0:08:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He was lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.52,0:09:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.82,0:09:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He's always waiting in front of\Nthe train station for a sucker.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.06,0:09:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be fooled by those types.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.80,0:09:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I was fooled?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.70,0:09:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The express train to Prague will be\Ndeparting from track seven at 3..15.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.98,0:09:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.29,0:09:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Thank you for helping me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.79,0:09:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.34,0:09:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.61,0:09:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it all right if I sit here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.22,0:10:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.43,0:10:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.33,0:10:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,To Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.15,0:10:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Japanese...aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.02,0:10:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.28,0:10:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Konnichiwa.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.82,0:10:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Domo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.89,0:10:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been to Japan before.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.32,0:10:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.79,0:10:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how many\Nyears it's been...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.59,0:10:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 1982, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.43,0:10:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah,\NI went to Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.50,0:10:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I ordered a lot of wire taps and\Nother high-tech gadgets.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.37,0:10:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, this song was popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.54,0:10:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.04,0:11:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kita no...\NHakaba doori na wa...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.91,0:11:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? That's not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.18,0:11:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kita no...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.89,0:11:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sakaba doori ni wa...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.65,0:11:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.16,0:11:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kita no...\NSakabadoori ni wa...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.70,0:11:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And there were robots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.87,0:11:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My son would have been happy if\NI had brought back a plastic model kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.44,0:11:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's your son now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.17,0:11:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh...\NHe died.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.72,0:11:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Entry inspection.\NPresent your passports.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.02,0:11:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.13,0:11:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Danke schön.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.81,0:12:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Elbe River.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.44,0:12:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How's the trout fishing\Nthis year?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.41,0:12:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Not very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.31,0:12:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Last year,\NI caught one this big.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.49,0:12:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be\Nimpossible this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.59,0:12:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Danke schön.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.33,0:12:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows you have\Na fake passport.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.91,0:12:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You should run away,\NDr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.95,0:12:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,H-How do you know me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.62,0:12:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.98,0:12:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The border police realized\Nthat your passport is a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.25,0:12:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They're coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.59,0:12:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You should get out\Nof here quick, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.74,0:13:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.78,0:13:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.98,0:13:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... S-Sorry.\NMy bag is too big and got caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.62,0:13:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.65,0:13:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.22,0:13:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Don't be rough!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.19,0:13:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What's in here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.39,0:13:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Important things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.03,0:13:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow! Ah, I got loose!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.14,0:13:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know where\Nthe other man went?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.11,0:13:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.81,0:13:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There was an Asian man\Nwith you in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.11,0:13:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows?\NHe probably went to the dining car.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.42,0:13:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, check the next car!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.12,0:13:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.82,0:13:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This is passenger car two.\NEmergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.16,0:14:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,An Asian passenger was\Nusing a fake passport!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.83,0:14:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.20,0:14:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?\N– Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.16,0:14:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop this train immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.79,0:14:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good. Very good!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.30,0:14:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They aren't chasing us this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.97,0:14:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The train stopped,\Nso I got off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.97,0:14:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... I forgot to introduce myself.\NI'm Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.88,0:14:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If you like, I can show you\Nthe way to the border, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.53,0:15:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm familiar with this area.\NI come here often to fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.86,0:15:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Climbing this mountain\Nis a bit rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.90,0:15:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can see familiar sights.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.04,0:15:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you help me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.34,0:15:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.57,0:15:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... I worked at a newspaper\Ncompany in East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.45,0:15:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now,\NI'm just a freelance journalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.82,0:15:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I read some articles on you.\NI was interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.52,0:15:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,False accusations were a part of\Neveryday life in East Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.06,0:15:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Political prisoners falsely charged...\NAccused murderers who aren't guilty...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.43,0:15:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of that, I can tell\Nwho's really guilty or innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.81,0:16:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You're innocent.\NIsn't that right, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.61,0:16:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you please stop\Ncalling me doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.18,0:16:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You're a brilliant neurosurgeon,\Naren't you, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.19,0:16:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm no longer a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.27,0:16:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?\NIt's a nice view, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.74,0:16:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We can tell if anyone's\Ncoming after us from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.74,0:16:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then.\NLet's take a bit of a break here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.18,0:16:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like a sandwich?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.62,0:16:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I also have wine!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.05,0:16:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And delicious cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.19,0:16:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No thank you. Umm...\NI don't have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.53,0:16:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun is still high.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.40,0:16:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better to cross the border\Nwhen it's dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.44,0:17:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Picnics are fun aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.07,0:17:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It nice to do this every so often,\Nright Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.45,0:17:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Delicious food and\Nan amazing view.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.32,0:17:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is when I can feel\Nthe pleasures of living.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.26,0:17:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I respect doctors like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.86,0:17:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Journalists like me can make people\Nhappy to be alive by writing good articles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.93,0:17:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can provide\Npeople with life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.04,0:17:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.34,0:17:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I shot a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.92,0:17:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Last month in Munich,\NI shot a man for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.70,0:18:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He probably died.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.03,0:18:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, I couldn't aim because\Nmy hands would tremble.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.07,0:18:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But once I shot him...\Nmy hands stopped trembling.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.18,0:18:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I have to\Nshoot another man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.39,0:18:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm...no longer a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.34,0:18:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever I go\Nto the Elbe River,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.78,0:18:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I think about how I would have\Nwanted to fish with my son here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.92,0:18:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Your dead son...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.76,0:19:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can catch trout this big.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.59,0:19:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He died without knowing\Nthe pleasures of fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.03,0:19:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He would have been saved if\Na doctor like you had been by his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.81,0:19:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But really, you can\Ncatch trout this big!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.19,0:19:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond that mountain\Nis the Czech border.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.83,0:19:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Past there, when you leave the forest\Npath, you might be able to get a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.70,0:19:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going back to\Nthe station from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.70,0:19:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYou were a real help, Mr. Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.34,0:19:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish you the best of luck,\NDr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.78,0:20:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If we meet again,\Nlet's have a picnic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.89,0:20:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.33,0:20:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone has their sins.\NThey don't go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.90,0:20:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But you must do,\Nwhat you must do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.93,0:20:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonderful...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.57,0:20:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.54,0:20:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the first time\NI've come here,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.01,0:21:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but at night, Prague looks like\Na village out of a fairytale.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.42,0:21:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me...\NIs it all right if I sit here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.36,0:21:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.86,0:21:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm completely\Ntaken by this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.23,0:21:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Mr. Pedrov, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.34,0:21:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You bought Russian citizenship
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.70,0:21:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and are currently living here\Nin the Czech Republic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.77,0:21:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I have some things\NI want to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.51,0:21:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you help me,\NMr. Pedrov?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.88,0:21:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No, your real name\Nis Reinhart Biermann.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.79,0:21:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a special orphanage\Nin East Berlin, wasn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.62,0:21:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an experimental lab where\Nscientific personality corrections
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.89,0:21:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,were performed on children.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.20,0:21:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,511 Kinderheim\NYou were the director there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.17,0:22:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You should know everything,\Nsince you were the director.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.04,0:22:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you trying to\Nachieve in East Berlin?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.72,0:22:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,At 511 Kinderheim...
